        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">General Register Office | Somerset House</hi></placeName>
                    <date>1868 Feb 27</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Rutland is our smallest county—&amp; the <hi rend="underline">proportions</hi> fluctuate from accidental causes—the extent of fluctuation varying with the numbers in relations which are expressed by a formula— given by the writers on probability. I enclose the numbers for Rutland—&amp; will shortly send you the proportions for all our counties.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>I am my dear Sir | yours very truly | W. Farr</p>
<p>P.S. The Registrar General to whom I mentioned your striking facts about the sexes of racehorses<ref target="#foot.f2"/>—inquired whether M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Darwin is acquainted with any known method for determining? He was told by a breeder that he possessed such a secret. <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/> <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/></p>
<p rend="left">C. Darwin Esq FRS</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
